data.enText: a S Asian dish of meat, vegetables, etc. cooked with hot spices, often served with rice

data.chText: 你再来一点咖喱烧菜好吗？
data.enText: Would you like some more curry?

data.chText: 以（肉或蔬菜）烹制咖喱烧菜
data.enText: to make curry out of meat or vegetables
to try to get sb to like or support you by praising or helping them a lot

means: 以(肉或蔬菜)烹制咖喱烧菜

data.enText: to try to get sb to like or support you by praising or helping them a lot

tr: (East Indian cookery) a pungent dish of vegetables or meats flavored with curry powder and usually eaten with rice
season with a mixture of spices

value.def: Curry is a dish composed of meat and vegetables, or just vegetables, in a sauce containing hot spices. It is usually eaten with rice and is one of the main dishes of India.

example.ex: I went for a curry last night.

value.tran: 咖喱菜(印度主要菜肴，常与米饭一起食用)

value.def: If one person tries to curry favour with another, they do things in order to try to gain their support or co-operation.

example.ex: Politicians are eager to promote their 'happy family' image to curry favour with voters.
example.tran: 政客们极力宣传他们的“幸福家庭”形象以讨好选民。

trans: 混合辣味调料粉；(尤指)咖喱粉
咖喱沙司；咖喱汁；咖喱酱；咖喱少司；咖哩酱
